Start Generating IDEAS: 2017 Competition Launches Oct 6
On Thursday, October 6th, this year's IDEAS Global Challenge will kick off
with the Fall Generator Dinner. RSVP on Eventbrite
<http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c4&i=
d=3D8abed855cb&e=3D7091d0658a>.
Join us for dinner. Pitch an idea or skill. Find a team. This is one of the
best opportunities to network with people across MIT interested in social
innovation and entrepreneurship!

We'll also be launching this year's special challenge on Inclusive Waste
Management
<http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c4&i=
d=3D1d74b501fe&e=3D7091d0658a>,
organized by D-Lab's Practical Impact Alliance.

Learn more about the IDEAS entry process and competition cyclehere
<http://mit.us6.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c4&=
id=3D8aca273eaf&e=3D7091d0658a>.
The first entry deadline is coming up on Thursday, October 27th.

If you're around Cambridge, we hope you'll join us at the dinner to find
out how you can get involved in IDEAS this year! And if you're not in the
area, learn about other ways to contribute below.
Summer Recap: IDEAS Winners Launch their Projects
Over the last several months, our 2016 winners were hard at work, launching
their projects and making a difference in communities around the world.
Some quick snapshots from the summer:

   - PrepHub Nepal met with communities in Kathmandu to understand
   post-disaster reconstruction and strategies to improve preparedness usin=
g
   traditional community structures. They shared some of their photos and
   updates on the MIT Student Instagram account!
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c=
4&id=3D4783e8359e&e=3D7091d0658a>
   - Bamboo Bicycles Beijing
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c=
4&id=3D8531e0f11f&e=3D7091d0658a>
ran
   a 6-week fellowship program with 8 students in China, teaching them
how tobuild
   their own bamboo bikes
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837=
c4&id=3D3af022ef1b&e=3D7091d0658a>
and
   working with them to develop their own community-based projects.
   - Tactile participated in Microsoft's #MakeWhatsNext Patent Program
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c=
4&id=3Ddf8d37f2de&e=3D7091d0658a>
for
   their braille-to-text converter, and helped to highlight the importance =
of
   women in STEM fields.
   - Ricult and dotLearn participated in the Martin Trust Center's delta V
   program
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837=
c4&id=3D64bfd248f1&e=3D7091d0658a>
-
   a capstone educational accelerator (along with a handful of other IDEAS
   participants! Watch their pitches from Demo Day here
   <http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c=
4&id=3D39039b1ad4&e=3D7091d0658a>
   .

We'll be checking in with the 2016 cohort periodically, and can't wait to
see what they accomplish over the course of their 15-month grants!
How to get involved
Become an IDEAS volunteer!
It=E2=80=99s all about collaboration. When passionate individuals pool thei=
r
skills, knowledge, and resources, we can tackle just about anything. IDEAS
teams have developed solutions to some of society=E2=80=99s most difficult =
problems
with the help of dedicated volunteers like you.

Among the most valuable resources that you can share are skills, knowledge,
and experience. Reach out to us if you would like to serve as a mentor,
reviewer, or event volunteer.

Read more about how you can help
<http://mit.us6.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c4&=
id=3Db42960ad45&e=3D7091d0658a>
and
consider signing up as a volunteer here
<http://mit.us6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dfbfcbe5f8114f808637f837c4&i=
d=3Dcb747bfc58&e=3D7091d0658a>
